	module.exports = "<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:\nnormal'><span lang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Ember by Kubbi - chiptune\nalbum of the year?<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span class=hps><b\nstyle='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:\nEN-US'>On February 5th, 2015,the Norwegian Gameboy- and computer musician </span></b></span><span\nlang=EN-GB><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.kubbimusic.com/\"><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:\nnormal'><span lang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Kubbi</span></b></a></span><b\nstyle='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:\nEN-US'> released his latest album called </span></b><span lang=EN-GB><a\ntarget=\"_blank\" href=\"https://kubbi.bandcamp.com/album/ember\"><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:\nnormal'><span lang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Ember</span></b></a></span><b\nstyle='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:\nEN-US'>. It's not often that I wait excitedly for a new release from a chiptune\nartist as much as this! <span class=hps>Will Kubbi meet my expectations</span>?\n<span class=hps>Will he raise the bar </span>once again, which he set so high\nwith </span></b><span lang=EN-GB><a\ntarget=\"_blank\" href=\"https://kubbi.bandcamp.com/album/circuithead\"><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:\nnormal'><span lang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Circuithead</span></b></a></span><b\nstyle='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span lang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:\nEN-US'>, his release from 2012? <span class=hps>Join me on my journey through\nthe fascinating universe of sounds created by a very exceptional artist</span>.<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><span lang=EN-GB><a\ntarget=\"_blank\" href=\"https://kubbi.bandcamp.com/album/ember\"><span lang=DE style='color:windowtext;\nmso-ansi-language:DE;mso-fareast-language:DE;mso-no-proof:yes;text-decoration:\nnone;text-underline:none'><span style='mso-ignore:vglayout'><img\nborder=0 width=605 x-height=241 src=\"./assets/articles/ember/image002.jpg\"\nalt=\"https://f1.bcbits.com/img/0004460005_10.jpg\" v:shapes=\"popupimage_image\"></span></span></a></span><span\nlang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>One thing's for sure: You'll never forget your\nfirst love! Remember the butterflies in your stomach, the exhilaration which\nallows you to suddenly walk through life in a total different way than before.\nAt the moment your senses are most sensitive, you recognize and feel many more\nthings than in the times before you entered into this special world of\nhappiness that love creates. When I heard the album </span><span lang=EN-GB><a\ntarget=\"_blank\" href=\"https://kubbi.bandcamp.com/album/circuithead\"><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Circuithead</span></a></span><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'> for the first time back in December 2012, made\nby an artist called Kubbi (of whom I've never heard before)the butterflies\ndefinitely started to fly again!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><b><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>A journey through time<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>At that time I had wanted to download an album\nfrom Bandcamp by some chiptune musician which I can't remember anymore. At the\ndownload page my eyes spotted some recommendations for other albums. </span><span\nlang=EN-GB><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://kubbi.bandcamp.com/album/circuithead\"><span\nlang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Circuithead</span></a> </span><span\nlang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>was one of these. It doesn´t have a\nspectacular cover artwork, but something inside me urged me to download this\nalbum as well. Thanks to the &quot;pay what you want&quot; option I was able to\nfeed my music player with a new album a few moments later. Today I would say\nthis must have been some sort of divine intervention.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>A few hours later my wallet was missing a few\nEuros. The money was well spent on <i style='mso-bidi-font-style:normal'>Circuithead</i>,\nbecause I was totally blown away by this album. Starting with the first track\nVegard Kummen, which is Kubbi's real name, it immediately caught my attention\nwith soulful melodies and the intense atmosphere created with fascinating\narrangements full of beeps, bleeps and amazing electronic sounds.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Perhaps it's now understandable, why I awaited\nthe 5th February of 2015 with so much excitement. This was the official release\ndate of Kubbi's new album </span><span lang=EN-GB><a\ntarget=\"_blank\" href=\"https://kubbi.bandcamp.com/album/ember\"><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Ember</span></a></span><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>, which is his first full length album since\nCircuithead. In the meantime new songs from him only appeared on various\nchiptune samplers, such as the popular </span><span lang=EN-GB><a\ntarget=\"_blank\" href=\"http://chiptuneswin.bandcamp.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Chiptune = WIN</span></a></span><span\nlang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'> series.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><span lang=EN-GB><a\ntarget=\"_blank\" href=\"https://kubbi.bandcamp.com/album/ember\"><span lang=DE style='color:windowtext;\nmso-ansi-language:DE;mso-fareast-language:DE;mso-no-proof:yes;text-decoration:\nnone;text-underline:none'><span style='mso-ignore:vglayout'><img\nborder=0 width=600 x-height=314 src=\"./assets/articles/ember/image003.jpg\"\nalt=\"http://ftp.4players.de/pub/pc/4sceners/Pics/Kubbi_Ember_CD.jpg\" v:shapes=\"Bild_x0020_1\"></span></span></a></span><span\nlang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><b><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Cooking blood<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Now let's have a closer look on </span><span\nlang=EN-GB><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://kubbi.bandcamp.com/album/ember\"><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Ember</span></a></span><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>. Consisting of a total of nine tracks </span><span\nlang=EN-GB><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://kubbi.bandcamp.com/album/ember\"><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Ember</span></a></span><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'> is available as digital download with the\noption to pay what you want for it. In addition it's also available as a\nphysical release on CD, featuring a good looking cover artwork. For $ 10.00 you\ncan call it yours.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>People who follow Kubbi's work will find a\ntrack already known on </span><span lang=EN-GB><a\ntarget=\"_blank\" href=\"https://kubbi.bandcamp.com/album/ember\"><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Ember</span></a></span><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>, which is called &quot;Restoration&quot;. A\ncouple of weeks before the official album release Kubbi had published this one\nas a teaser track on his Soundcloud page. A clever idea, as the song is so\nbeautiful, it's actually hard to stop listening to it. Restoration builds up to\na great atmosphere right from the beginning with calm ambient sounds. Later the\nsong structure gets more and more complex. Squeaky chiptune sounds come in,\nbuilding more lovely melodies and successfully try to intensify the\naforementioned butterflies and the embers<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'> \n</span>start to ignite inside you. Restoration features all the markings of what\nmakes a real Kubbi tune. It's like some sort of wellbeing for your body, your\nsoul; even for your heart. I realized after some seconds of listening, that\nKubbi could write history with this album!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span class=hps><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Restoration is </span></span><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>proof of how much <span class=hps>Vegard Kummen</span>'s\nskill for arrangement and melody has evolved during the last two years. The new\ntracks sound even better than his old output, the song structure is richer and\nmore complex than ever before and there's always a little surprise for you the\nlonger a tune continues to play. Sometimes strings are added in a perfect way\nto the backbone of the 8-bit sounds and electronic sequences, then drums change\nfrom mid tempo to drum 'n' bass style or some e-guitar riffs transport the\nmelodies into much higher spheres. It's s quite<span style='mso-spacerun:yes'> \n</span>breathtaking!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:\nnormal'><span lang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Soft rock<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal style='text-align:justify'><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>The guitar is a really important component on\nthis album and the main characterizing instrument besides the Gameboy. Saying\nthat, while there's no guitar, a steel drum is used in &quot;Pathfinder&quot;,\nwhich is the opening track of the new album and this expands the musical\nexperience for the listener in a great way, the second track on\n&quot;Ember&quot; really excels in playing around with a plectrum effectively.\nThis leads to the fine guitar sounds avoiding hitting your nerves, but instead\nachieves a perfect vibe and develops into some wonderful and perfect melodies.\nIt's clear that you shouldn't expect real hard rock music on </span><span\nlang=EN-GB><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://kubbi.bandcamp.com/album/ember\"><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Ember</span></a></span><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>. Kubbi is a cuddly musician. His language is\ncalled melody. A skillful arrangement of atmospheric melodies at that! The\norigin of chiptune sounds is always present, but guitars and drums just enrich\nthe listening experience.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><span lang=EN-GB><a\ntarget=\"_blank\" href=\"http://www.kubbimusic.com/\"><span lang=DE style='color:windowtext;\nmso-ansi-language:DE;mso-fareast-language:DE;mso-no-proof:yes;text-decoration:\nnone;text-underline:none'><span style='mso-ignore:vglayout'><img\nborder=0 width=600 x-height=278 src=\"./assets/articles/ember/image004.jpg\"\nalt=\"http://ftp.4players.de/pub/pc/4sceners/Pics/Kubbi-Slide-Studio-No-Text.jpg\"\nv:shapes=\"Bild_x0020_4\"></span></span></a></span><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Kubbi\nreaches his wildest and hardest stage with track number 3 which is called\n&quot;Firelight&quot;. Here he rocks faster and harder than before and later on\nwith the other tracks on the album. <span class=hps>That is refreshing</span>,\nbut also <span class=hps>familiar</span>, <span class=hps>because his Gameboy still</span>\nis <span class=hps>the lead singer</span> and everybody can't stop looking at its\nlips.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Kubbi also\nknows how to go with stuff which is hot at the moment. With the song\n&quot;Cascade&quot; he follows the trendy dubstep style a bit, but also goes\nalong with nice melodies utilizing 8bit sounds effectively. This formulates a\nreally fresh listening experience, because you can't get the beautiful melody\nout of your head, while your feet automatically start to stamp to the rhythm of\nthe wubwubwub passages.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Other\ntracks like &quot;Compass&quot; and the outstanding &quot;Overworld&quot;\nrenounce any mentioned experiments. Kubbi is doing here exactly for what he's\nknown best: tinkering sounds together which are filled with harmony, enthusiasm\nand love, where the magical structure of sounds won't let you leave the private\nlistening room he's created for you.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Another great\nsong on </span><span lang=EN-GB><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://kubbi.bandcamp.com/album/ember\"><span\nlang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Ember</span></a></span><span\nlang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>, which is called &quot;The\nCairn&quot; is already known from the sampler </span><span lang=EN-GB><a\ntarget=\"_blank\" href=\"http://chiptuneswin.bandcamp.com/album/magfest-win\"><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>MAGFest = Win</span></a></span><span class=hps><span\nlang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>. The final track on </span></span><span\nlang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Kubbi's latest release <span\nclass=hps>is called &quot;Formed by Glaciers&quot; and is the quietest tune of\nthe bunch. Known melodies are reused here using different instruments and\nsounds to give new insights into Kubbi's world of audio. Driven by the sounds\nof Erin McQuisten's graceful voice and a piano, a massive inferno slowly starts\nto burn and build while playing this song. It's a perfect symphony, short but\nviolent, to end </span></span><span lang=EN-GB><a\ntarget=\"_blank\" href=\"https://kubbi.bandcamp.com/album/ember\"><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Ember</span></a></span><span class=hps><span\nlang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>. You can't help but love what this\noutstanding artist is doing.<o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><b><span lang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Conclusion</span></b><span\nlang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>It wasn't\neasy to raise the bar again which Kubbi had set with his previous album </span><span\nlang=EN-GB><a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://kubbi.bandcamp.com/album/circuithead\"><span\nlang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Circuithead</span></a></span><span\nlang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>, but </span><span lang=EN-GB><a\ntarget=\"_blank\" href=\"https://kubbi.bandcamp.com/album/ember\"><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Ember</span></a> </span><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>achieves it. I can gladly speak up here – this\nis a modern chiptune album that may be regarded as a milestone due to the\nwonderful melodies included and the atmosphere it's achieves as it builds up. If\nyou really want to do Kubbi a reproach you could say that he's often composing\nmusic using the same formula. Most tracks start slowly and a bit quiet and as\nthey develop more and more instruments are added until the full song explodes\nin its full glory towards the end. But is this really worth griping about? Of\ncourse not, because this formula works. Always! That's the true spirit and\npower of Kubbi and this is the way to catch everyone's heart. Mine is yours,\nKubbi. Forever!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><span lang=EN-GB><a\ntarget=\"_blank\" href=\"https://kubbi.bandcamp.com/album/ember\"><span lang=DE style='color:windowtext;\nmso-ansi-language:DE;mso-fareast-language:DE;mso-no-proof:yes;text-decoration:\nnone;text-underline:none'><span style='mso-ignore:vglayout'><img\nborder=0 width=400 x-height=400 src=\"./assets/articles/ember/image006.jpg\"\nalt=\"http://ftp.4players.de/pub/pc/4sceners/Pics/Kubbi-Ember-cover.png\" v:shapes=\"Bild_x0020_7\"></span></span></a></span><span\nlang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:\nauto;text-align:center;line-height:normal'><u><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Track list:<br>\n</span></u><span lang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>1. Pathfinder<br>\n2. Ember<br>\n3.Firelight<br>\n4.Cascade<br>\n5.Compass<br>\n6.Overworld<br>\n7.The Cairn<br>\n8.Restoration<br>\n9. Formed by Glaciers<u><o:p></o:p></u></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><span lang=EN-GB><a\nhref=\"https://kubbi.bandcamp.com/album/ember\" target=\"_blank\"><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Ember @ Bandcamp</span></a></span><span\nlang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'><br>\n</span><span lang=EN-GB><a href=\"http://www.kubbimusic.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><span\nlang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>KubbiOffical Website</span></a></span><span\nlang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'><br>\n<br>\n<b style='mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>Personal Favourites:</b> Ember,\nOverworld, Restoration<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal align=right style='margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt;\ntext-align:right'><a name=\"_GoBack\"></a><em><span lang=EN-US style='font-family:\n\"Calibri\",\"sans-serif\";mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:\nminor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;\nmso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Thanks to ne7 for proof-reading and correcting the\ntranslation.<o:p></o:p></span></em></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal align=right style='text-align:right'><i style='mso-bidi-font-style:\nnormal'><span lang=EN-US style='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'>Image source: Kubbi<o:p></o:p></span></i></p>\n\n<p class=MsoNormal align=center style='text-align:center'><span lang=EN-US\nstyle='mso-ansi-language:EN-US'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\n"

